[{"sha":"defb2786ef511acdd27a328275b9b62c215817e8","node_id":"C_kwDOAb3RHtoAKGRlZmIyNzg2ZWY1MTFhY2RkMjdhMzI4Mjc1YjliNjJjMjE1ODE3ZTg","commit":{"author":{"name":"Asim Aslam","email":"asim@aslam.me","date":"2026-05-10T16:14:04Z"},"committer":{"name":"GitHub","email":"noreply@github.com","date":"2026-05-10T16:14:04Z"},"message":" update AI provider documentation (#2897)\n\n* feat: add prometheus monitoring wrapper\n\nReintroduces the Prometheus metrics wrapper previously available in the\nplugins repository, updated for go-micro v5. Exposes request count and\nlatency histograms for handlers, subscribers, and outgoing client calls\nvia NewHandlerWrapper, NewSubscriberWrapper, NewCallWrapper and\nNewClientWrapper, labelled with service/endpoint/status.\n\nOptions cover namespace, subsystem, const labels, histogram buckets and\na custom registerer; duplicate collectors (e.g. from multiple wrappers\nsharing the same config) are reused transparently via a cached\nmetrics bundle.\n\nFixes #2893\n\n* fix(registry/etcd): clear lease/register caches on KeepAlive channel closure\n\nWhen the etcd client's long-lived KeepAlive channel closes (e.g. because\nthe lease expired on the server side during a network partition), the\nprevious cleanup only removed the channel bookkeeping. The stale entries\nin `leases` and `register` caused the next registerNode() heartbeat to\nhit the \"unchanged hash\" short-circuit and skip re-registration entirely,\nso the service permanently disappeared from etcd.\n\nExtract the cleanup into handleKeepAliveClosed and also drop the cached\nlease id and hash so the next heartbeat performs a full Grant+Put and\nthe service recovers within one RegisterInterval.\n\nRegression introduced by #2822; fix is symmetric with the existing\nsynchronous KeepAliveOnce recovery path that propagates\nrpctypes.ErrLeaseNotFound.\n\n* docs: add AI provider integration guide and Supported AI Providers section\n\nAdd a step-by-step guide for AI infrastructure companies to implement\nai.Model and contribute a provider to go-micro. Covers the full\nlifecycle: skeleton, tool call handling, tests, registration, and PR\nchecklist.\n\nAdd a \"Supported AI Providers\" section to the project README that lists\ncurrent providers (Anthropic, OpenAI) in a table and links to the\nintegration guide with a call-to-action for new providers and sponsors.\n\nStreamline the \"Adding a New Provider\" section in ai/README.md to point\nto the new guide instead of duplicating a full code listing.\n\n* Update contribution guidelines in README.md\n\nRemoved Discord contact information for platform contributions.\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>","tree":{"sha":"8ddff09ed5362ccc237572267fc8cc67328cbb3f","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/micro/go-micro/git/trees/8ddff09ed5362ccc237572267fc8cc67328cbb3f"},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/micro/go-micro/git/commits/defb2786ef511acdd27a328275b9b62c215817e8","comment_count":0,"verification":{"verified":true,"reason":"valid","signature":"-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\nwsFcBAABCAAQBQJqAK7MCRC1aQ7uu5UhlAAA4mMQACaJ/T7XwjB4dZIRgBpdw45m\nz4SH/ehCYMwDCL2c27773N1pEcTNzfUrTLiwRSiNmnlLezyxxg2SFGPRyPe2hN71\n/ZZmk0YQlokrwEFFt77PbkJvxh1Mhsq3NWJwwO/p4xT62Vz8FjLToOd44C6CbP7f\nSmn4RZ5lyqg4MsblV/nJxMZwp/5OQynXen6LxixBiOdSPFimFVx61vTxQ9hVo6hX\nrUgv5yBF6rR51hdhYpU80Iwu6/874KQeGbhzUFVG6EM/vuypZsxuQk71KaD2cDBw\nt1nTP7dAdTDV+X2RykcXrxn8It3UneV826BQNzCUbtWMW0T64YVOhHI3rqy36n/+\n0XfnuCfUlcFqnaiuzdQr8X5XAPGePQELAjEgwv4rvcTVjl7jODdvCboXPQrQ7VWW\nZWCEr4i3BcQxr19WPTM2ysNGuhy/UYw4lxweI8UwsdZA61843J/HjtotveEz9h6P\nQRPrZXBqHHPBJ6IVm7dqfweYXchsopkmcIkW8EOAKPt8vil9B9/W/klfYTn3Tbwf\nd5lEQlentlXUKJ2XfkwrBqs1MSWPM2wlIttaACh6VQfEKdg9zuP253Eu9cz8OFj1\nvMouIA5pOrBvrbbPjoHAOVpz6Oh5WpATm+dmQF2G5QQKgtE1VysHhc1N/92tt3/0\nlu18AYGznsCQkyhEjYLc\n=nN1P\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----\n","payload":"tree 8ddff09ed5362ccc237572267fc8cc67328cbb3f\nparent 15cc876848f407aae05941ca301354b5a8fedaa6\nauthor Asim Aslam <asim@aslam.me> 1778429644 +0100\ncommitter GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1778429644 +0100\n\n update AI provider documentation (#2897)\n\n* feat: add prometheus monitoring wrapper\n\nReintroduces the Prometheus metrics wrapper previously available in the\nplugins repository, updated for go-micro v5. Exposes request count and\nlatency histograms for handlers, subscribers, and outgoing client calls\nvia NewHandlerWrapper, NewSubscriberWrapper, NewCallWrapper and\nNewClientWrapper, labelled with service/endpoint/status.\n\nOptions cover namespace, subsystem, const labels, histogram buckets and\na custom registerer; duplicate collectors (e.g. from multiple wrappers\nsharing the same config) are reused transparently via a cached\nmetrics bundle.\n\nFixes #2893\n\n* fix(registry/etcd): clear lease/register caches on KeepAlive channel closure\n\nWhen the etcd client's long-lived KeepAlive channel closes (e.g. because\nthe lease expired on the server side during a network partition), the\nprevious cleanup only removed the channel bookkeeping. The stale entries\nin `leases` and `register` caused the next registerNode() heartbeat to\nhit the \"unchanged hash\" short-circuit and skip re-registration entirely,\nso the service permanently disappeared from etcd.\n\nExtract the cleanup into handleKeepAliveClosed and also drop the cached\nlease id and hash so the next heartbeat performs a full Grant+Put and\nthe service recovers within one RegisterInterval.\n\nRegression introduced by #2822; fix is symmetric with the existing\nsynchronous KeepAliveOnce recovery path that propagates\nrpctypes.ErrLeaseNotFound.\n\n* docs: add AI provider integration guide and Supported AI Providers section\n\nAdd a step-by-step guide for AI infrastructure companies to implement\nai.Model and contribute a provider to go-micro. Covers the full\nlifecycle: skeleton, tool call handling, tests, registration, and PR\nchecklist.\n\nAdd a \"Supported AI Providers\" section to the project README that lists\ncurrent providers (Anthropic, OpenAI) in a table and links to the\nintegration guide with a call-to-action for new providers and sponsors.\n\nStreamline the \"Adding a New Provider\" section in ai/README.md to point\nto the new guide instead of duplicating a full code listing.\n\n* Update contribution guidelines in README.md\n\nRemoved Discord contact information for platform contributions.\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>","verified_at":"2026-05-10T16:14:05Z"}},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/micro/go-micro/commits/defb2786ef511acdd27a328275b9b62c215817e8","html_url":"https://github.com/micro/go-micro/commit/defb2786ef511acdd27a328275b9b62c215817e8","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/micro/go-micro/commits/defb2786ef511acdd27a328275b9b62c215817e8/comments","author":{"login":"asim","id":17530,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3NTMw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/17530?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/asim","html_url":"https://github.com/asim","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/asim/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/asim/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/asim/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/asim/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/asim/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/asim/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/asim/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/asim/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/asim/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"committer":{"login":"web-flow","id":19864447,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE5ODY0NDQ3","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/19864447?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow","html_url":"https://github.com/web-flow","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/followers","follo